# Whisper Journal

Whisper Journal is a personal diary mobile application built with **React Native** and **Expo**. It allows users to **record audio notes**, **write text notes**, and organize their thoughts securely and conveniently. The app features a sleek UI, custom fonts, and smooth navigation for an enjoyable journaling experience.

---

## Features

- **Audio Recording:** Record and save personal audio entries.
- **Text Notes:** Write and store diary entries in text form.
- **Navigation:** Easy navigation between Home, Library, Write, and Note Details screens.
- **Custom Fonts:** Uses a custom font (`Quicksand-Regular`) for a modern look.
- **Splash Screen:** Attractive splash screen displayed on app launch.
- **Journal Organization:** View all entries in a clean, organized layout.

---

## Screens

1. **Home Screen** – Dashboard overview of recent journal entries.  
2. **Library Screen** – List and search through previous notes and recordings.  
3. **Write Screen** – Create a new audio or text entry.  
4. **Note Details** – View a single note with its full content or audio playback.  

---

## Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Joseph-Godwin12/whisper-journal.git
cd whisper-journal
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
# or
yarn install
Start the Expo project:

bash
Copy code
expo start
Scan the QR code with the Expo Go app on your phone or run on an emulator.

Project Structure
bash
Copy code
whisper-journal/
│
├─ assets/
│  └─ fonts/
│     └─ Quicksand-Regular.ttf
│
├─ components/
│  └─ CustomText.tsx       # Custom Text component with global font
│
├─ context/
│  └─ JournalContext.tsx   # State management for journal entries
│
├─ navigation/
│  └─ AppNavigator.tsx     # Stack and Tab navigation
│
├─ Screens/
│  ├─ HomeScreen.tsx
│  ├─ LibraryScreen.tsx
│  ├─ WriteScreen.tsx
│  ├─ NoteDetailsScreen.tsx
│  └─ SplashScreen.tsx
│
├─ App.tsx
└─ package.json
Technologies Used
React Native – Mobile app framework.

Expo – Development and build platform.

TypeScript – Static type checking.

React Navigation – Stack and Tab navigation.

Expo Font – Custom font support.

React Context – State management for journal entries.

How to Use
Open the app to see the splash screen.

Navigate to Write Screen to create a new text or audio note.

Visit the Library Screen to view, search, and manage all your previous entries.

Tap any note to see it in full detail on the Note Details Screen.

